{"questionId":"13917851","questionHtml":"<p>By using&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>,&nbsp;solve the differential equation to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>. You may assume that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>separating variables&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mo>d</mo><mi>s</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>s</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>s</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>rearranging to make <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> the subject&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em> for making <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> the subject of their equation and not just an attempt, or an erroneous equation with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> also on the RHS.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mi>k</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>applying initial conditions (here or elsewhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi></mrow><mi>k</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>100</mn><mi>k</mi></math></p>\n<p>so</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>100</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mi>k</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13917851","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.1ci","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"By using dvdt=vdvds, solve the differential equation to find v in terms of s, g and k. You may assume that g-kv2>0.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.11—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.14—Setting up a DE, solve by separating variables","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}